<tree mode="full" root="false" taxon="Definition"><frontmatter><trail/> <anchor>12937</anchor> <addr>jms-0033</addr>  <route>jms-0033.xml</route> <date>March 5, 2023</date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Carrable map</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A morphism <tex>{ E } \xrightarrow{p} { B }</tex> in a category <tex>\mathcal{C}</tex> is said to be <em>carrable</em> when for any <tex>{ A } \xrightarrow{f} { B }</tex>, the pullback <tex>{ E \times _{B}A } \xrightarrow{f^*p} { A }</tex> depicted below exists.</p><center><img src="resources/416e4490fdee5ae3be63be765b5046b4-web.svg"/></center></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree mode="full" root="false" taxon="Definition"><frontmatter><trail/> <anchor>12939</anchor> <addr>jms-0031</addr>  <route>jms-0031.xml</route> <date>March 5, 2023</date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Exponentiable arrow</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="jms-0033.xml" type="local">carrable map</link> <tex>{ E } \xrightarrow{p} { B }</tex> in a category <tex>\mathcal{C}</tex> is said to be <em>exponentiable</em> when it is <link href="jms-0032.xml" type="local">exponentiable</link> when viewed as an object of the slice category <tex>{ \mathcal{C} } _{ / B }</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>